column2: (SELECT valeur FROM t_ct_conf WHERE nom='ct_1_liv') ::text AS ct_liv,

column3: (SELECT ad_ban_id FROM t_adresse GROUP BY ad_ban_id HAVING count(*) > 1) AS AD2

column1: 'Distance trop importante entre le noeud qui porte le SUF et son adresse' ::text AS ct_def,
'Distance : ' || cast(ST_Distance(vsf.geom, ad.geom) as integer) ::text AS ct_detail,
(SELECT valeur FROM t_ct_conf WHERE nom='ct_1_liv') ::text AS ct_liv,

column3: left join t_adresse as ad on vsf.sf_ad_code = ad.ad_code,
(select valeur as dist from t_ct_conf where nom = 'sf_ad_code : distance maximale entre le SUF et l adresse') as conf

column2: and ST_Distance(vsf.geom, ad.geom) > CAST(conf.dist AS INTEGER)
--sous requete pour le parametre de tolerance
where nom = 'cl_geom : distance maximale entre les extremites d un cable et une bp ou lt'),
-- sous requete pour trouver tous les cables qui ont une BPE a leur point de depart

column3: OR ST_DWITHIN(ST_EndPoint(cl.geom), lt.geom, cast(conf.tol as float8))
OR ST_DWITHIN(ST_EndPoint(cl.geom), pto.geom, cast(conf.tol as float8))

column2: -- sous requete pour trouver tous les cables qui ont une BPE a leur point de fin

column3: OR ST_DWITHIN(ST_EndPoint(cl.geom), lt.geom, cast(conf.tol as float8))
OR ST_DWITHIN(ST_EndPoint(cl.geom), pto.geom, cast(conf.tol as float8))

column1: 'Les extremites du cable ne sont pas reliees geographiquement a une BPE ou un LT' ::text AS ct_def,
(SELECT valeur FROM t_ct_conf WHERE nom='ct_1_liv') ::text AS ct_liv,
from   vs_elem_cl_cb as cbl LEFT JOIN CablDepartOK ON cbl.cl_code = CablDepartOK.cl_code

column8: LEFT JOIN CablFinOK ON cbl.cl_code = CablFinOK.cl_code
